From {{ME.}} {{term|abissus|lang=enm}} < {{L.}} {{term|abyssus||a bottomless gulf|lang=la}} < {{AGr.}} {{term|sc=polytonic|ἄβυσσος||tr=abyssos|bottomless|lang=grc}} {{term|sc=polytonic|ἀ-||tr=a-|not|lang=grc}}+ {{term|sc=polytonic|βυσσός||tr=bysso|depth|lang=grc}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|/ə-bĭs'/}}, {{IPA|/əˈbɪs/}} {{SAMPA|/@"bIs/}}
* {{audio|en-us-abyss.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|es}}

# A bottomless or [[unfathomed]] depth, gulf, or [[chasm]]; hence, any deep, [[immeasurable]], and, specifically, [[hell]], or the [[bottomless pit]].
# [[infinite|Infinite]] time; a vast intellectual or moral depth.
# {{heraldry}} The center of an [[escutcheon]].

====Quotations====
{{seeCites}}

====Usage notes====
This word, in its leading uses, is associated with the [[cosmological]] [[notions]] of the Hebrews, having reference to a supposed {{term|illimitable}} mass of waters from which our earth [[sprung]], and beneath whose [[profound]] depths the wicked were [[punished]]. - [[Encyclopedia Britannica]]

